attributes.Long form description: First, the student detaches the Joy-Con controllers and attaches them into the Joy-Con comfort grip with the instructor's help. Then, the student detaches the Joy-Con controllers from the Joy-Con comfort grip to attach them to the Joy-Con straps. Then, the student detaches the Joy-Con controllers from the Joy-Con straps to attach them to the Nintendo Switch console. After that, the student stands the Nintendo Switch on the table using the kickstand. Then, the student exchanges the game card for another one. After that, the student exchanges the SD card of the Nintendo Switch console for a new one. Then, the student turns on the console. Last, the student turns the Nintendo Switch off but needs the help of the instructor to do it correctly.

attributes.Transcription: We will now operate the Nintendo Switch.
The first task is to change the controller from the handheld mode to the Joy-Con comfort grip.

attributes.Action sentence: The student inspects the Nintendo Switch components on the table.

attributes.Transcription: First, you have to take the colored parts off the display.
There's a black button at the back of the colored parts which you press and you slide it off.
And you can slide it up or down.
And the grip is the one that you see in the middle there.
